main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Kansas City, Missouri, on September 24, 2002.
interesting points: The object was reported to have a daylight sighting and was observed for 2-3 minutes,The object was seen moving from south to north at a high speed,No physical evidence or photographs were collected during the observation,The sighting falls under Project 10073 record,The report concluded that there was insufficient data to reach a conclusion regarding the sighting.
